n officially install apps on your Android TV in two ways. First, you can open Google Play directly on Android TV and search for your desired app. Second, you can remotely install an app on your Android TV using Google Play on your Android phone.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eThe latter is thanks to the ability to \u003ca href=\"https://www.makeuseof.com/remote-install-apps-on-other-android-devices-play-store-app/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eremotely install apps on other devices using Google Play\u003c/a\u003e. It provides the best and easiest way to install apps if you also have an Android device. Like Android on smartphones and tablets, Android TV is also permissive to installing apps from third-party marketplaces. If the official channels are insufficient, you can easily \u003ca href=\"https://www.makeuseof.com/how-to-sideload-apps-on-android-tv/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003esideload apps on Android TV\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"less-bloatware\"\u003e\n            \u003cspan\u003e3 \u003c/span\u003e\n        \u003cspan\u003e\n                            Less Bloatware\n                    \u003c/span\u003e\n       \u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAnother likable aspect of Android TV is less bloat; Android TV has way fewer pre-installed apps. Although this varies depending on the TV manufacturer, there are generally fewer additional apps installed that you don\u0026#39;t need.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eIt has a minimal list of pre-installed apps, and most of these are actually useful. For instance, there\u0026#39;s no denying that video streaming apps like Amazon Prime Video, Netflix, and YouTube are useful and quicker to access if pre-installed.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"google-tv-interface-refined-the-user-experience\"\u003e\n            \u003cspan\u003e4 \u003c/span\u003e\n        \u003cspan\u003e\n                            Google TV Interface Refined the User Experience\n                    \u003c/span\u003e\n       \u003c/h2\u003e\n   